# ComfyJS

**ComfyJS** is an open‐source JavaScript library that makes it incredibly easy to connect to Twitch chat and respond to messages, commands, and events.

## Key Features
- **Simplicity:** Set up a basic Twitch chat listener in one line of code.
- **Chat Commands Handling:** Easily define custom commands.
- **Multiple Environments:** Works both in Node.js and in the browser.
- **Extensible & Event-Rich:** Supports various Twitch events such as subs, raids, and more.

## Setup Guide

### For Node.js:
1. **Install the package:**
```bash
npm install comfy.js --save
```

2. **Initialize the library:**
```JavaScript
const ComfyJS = require("comfy.js");
ComfyJS.Init("YourTwitchChannel");
```

3. **Add event handlers:**
```JavaScript
ComfyJS.onCommand = (user, command, message, flags, extra) => {
  if (command === "dice") {
    const roll = Math.floor(Math.random() * 6) + 1;
    console.log(`${user} rolled a ${roll}`);
  }
};
```

### For Browser:
1. **Include via CDN:**
```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/comfy.js@latest/dist/comfy.min.js"></script>
```

2. Initialize and add event listeners as above.

## Example Usage

A simple command bot that greets users and responds to `!uptime`:

```JavaScript
ComfyJS.onChat = (user, message) => {
  if (message.toLowerCase().includes("hello")) {
    ComfyJS.Say(`Hello @${user}!`);
  }
};

ComfyJS.onCommand = (user, command) => {
  if (command === "uptime") {
    ComfyJS.Say(`@${user}, the stream has been live for 2 hours!`);
  }
};

ComfyJS.Init("YourTwitchChannel");
```

For more details, check out the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/instafluff/ComfyJS).

